2500|$|The {{beginning}} of the Occupy Movement was reliant on the usage of <b>social</b> media <b>accounts</b> for the dispersal of information. These accounts were very useful and helped tremendously. The <b>social</b> media <b>accounts</b> eventually became hierarchical and failed their purpose. Some [...] believe, {{in order to have}} been more successful, the <b>social</b> media <b>accounts</b> should have been more heavily regulated and kept to a standard.|$|R
